1
00:00:18,670 --> 00:00:19,730
Forced mate! Mate!

2
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:24,960
Nice move this round.

3
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
You're trading cannons, huh?

4
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,600
Yeah. It's time to trade.

5
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:41,470
Gentlemen.

6
00:00:41,670 --> 00:00:43,000
Can I ask you something?

7
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:46,670
How do I get to Xia Gang's place?
The one from the shipyard.

8
00:00:46,670 --> 00:00:48,910
Go all the way in and then turn right.

9
00:00:49,110 --> 00:00:50,640
First one on the left.

10
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:53,690
Why are you looking for Xia?

11
00:00:56,110 --> 00:00:57,640
Bring out the rook.

12
00:00:59,260 --> 00:01:00,180
Check.

13
00:03:18,410 --> 00:03:22,730
[THE GUILTY]

14
00:03:23,230 --> 00:03:25,930
[Episode 5]

15
00:03:57,290 --> 00:04:04,310
[Flower Shop]

16
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:11,670
[Waiting for you in the forest at Lover's Peak at 9 p.m.]

17
00:05:12,010 --> 00:05:12,960
Lu Ming.

18
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:23,200
[Flower Shop]

19
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:27,820
Where's Lu Ming?

20
00:05:30,510 --> 00:05:32,190
I knocked, but he wasn't home.

21
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,640
Have you seen him?

22
00:05:34,830 --> 00:05:36,580
I haven't seen him either.

23
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:18,460
[Tomb of Xia Gang, a loving father]

24
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:20,260
What happened to the tombstone?

25
00:06:23,050 --> 00:06:24,730
Who did this?

26
00:06:26,130 --> 00:06:27,460
It's messed up.

27
00:06:48,430 --> 00:06:50,230
[Tomb of Xia Gang, a loving father]

28
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,480
Xia Xue!

29
00:07:04,190 --> 00:07:05,560
I know it's you.

30
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,550
Stop hiding.

31
00:07:11,010 --> 00:07:11,760
Xia Xue.

32
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,870
Stop hiding. Come out!

33
00:07:16,670 --> 00:07:17,240
Stop!

34
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:18,560
Lu Ming!

35
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,480
Stop hitting me!

36
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:21,810
Or I'll call the police!

37
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,480
I know you killed Ma Ke.

38
00:07:29,850 --> 00:07:32,010
I have the videotape.

39
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,120
[Tomb of Xia Gang, a loving father]

40
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:39,790
Xia,

41
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,050
everything's fine.

42
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:42,480
Don't worry.

43
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,360
Let's go.

44
00:07:47,930 --> 00:07:49,260
Let's wait a bit longer.

45
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:50,690
Lu Ming hasn't come yet.

46
00:07:51,870 --> 00:07:53,780
He's not that unreliable.

47
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,040
Something urgent must have come up.

48
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,690
I'll get someone to fix this tomorrow.

49
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,040
Can it be fixed?

50
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:05,870
Yes, it can.

51
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:10,550
Where have you been?

52
00:08:10,580 --> 00:08:11,980
Why are you only here now?

53
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:15,790
I overslept.

54
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:17,430
Don't you know what day it is?

55
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:18,070
And you overslept?

56
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:18,930
Unbelievable.

57
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:20,920
You overslept?

58
00:08:21,430 --> 00:08:23,290
Hurry up and offer incense to Xia.

59
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,380
Are you okay?

60
00:08:31,530 --> 00:08:32,320
I'm fine.

61
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:11,180
[Tomb of Xia Gang, a loving father]

62
00:09:19,310 --> 00:09:20,040
Let's go.

63
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,400
When are you going back to Huacheng?

64
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:33,880
I'll wait a bit longer.

65
00:09:34,380 --> 00:09:35,780
What are you waiting for?

66
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:40,080
I still have some things to take care of.

67
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:41,670
What things?

68
00:09:42,930 --> 00:09:44,190
My personal business.

69
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:45,810
Stay out of it.

70
00:09:58,260 --> 00:09:59,130
Move!

71
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,970
Kill me if you have the guts.

72
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:08,810
Tomorrow, someone will take the tape
to the police.

73
00:10:08,810 --> 00:10:10,410
And all three of you will die.

74
00:10:11,650 --> 00:10:12,600
What do you want?

75
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:15,840
If I give the tape to Ma Derong,

76
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:18,400
how much do you think he'd pay me?

77
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:21,390
How much do you want?

78
00:10:21,790 --> 00:10:23,320
It's simple.

79
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:26,060
Two hundred thousand.

80
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:29,880
In exchange for the lives
of the three of you.

81
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:32,390
I don't have money.

82
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:34,750
Three lives, for heaven's sake!

83
00:10:41,170 --> 00:10:42,320
[Enforcement Bureau
of the Nanping City People’s Court]

84
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,310
Chen Hu.

85
00:10:43,630 --> 00:10:45,390
Do you have any legal document
writing jobs?

86
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:46,650
What's wrong, Lu Ming?

87
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,670
Nothing.

88
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:51,080
Go ask at the entrance of Nanping Court.

89
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:51,840
It seems like

90
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,270
lots of people there need legal advice.

91
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:53,630
Hello, do you need documents drafted?

92
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:54,600
[Law student's legal consultation
and document drafting services]

93
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,440
No, no.

94
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,080
Do you need documents drafted?

95
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:58,910
No, no.

96
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:00,400
[People's Procuratorate of Nanping City]

97
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,320
Hello. Legal advice, document drafting?

98
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:02,910
No.

99
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:06,680
Hello.

100
00:11:07,390 --> 00:11:08,440
Here's my card.

101
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:37,970
Brother.

102
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,310
I majored in law in college.

103
00:11:40,550 --> 00:11:42,050
I'll definitely be cheaper than them.

104
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:43,000
Drafting documents,

105
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,600
legal advice, I can do it all.

106
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:48,360
The foreman won't pay.
Can you get the money back?

107
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:50,810
You'll have to give me the details.

108
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,630
I have a cousin

109
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:55,050
who works as a diver
at a construction site.

110
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:58,120
A few days ago, he went into
a foundation pit to retrieve a drill bit.

111
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,150
They had a deal.

112
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,820
If he goes down and comes up,
he gets 10,000.

113
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:05,020
If he goes down and doesn't come back up,
he gets a million.

114
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:08,110
In the end, he died in the pit.

115
00:12:08,110 --> 00:12:08,910
How much?

116
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,320
A million.

117
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:11,960
I mean, if he came back up.

118
00:12:12,820 --> 00:12:13,620
Ten thousand.

119
00:12:15,550 --> 00:12:17,280
Who's qualified to do this job?

120
00:12:17,890 --> 00:12:20,250
Good swimmers who aren't afraid of death.

121
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,030
Coming.

122
00:12:40,030 --> 00:12:40,720
Xue.

123
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:41,270
Auntie.

124
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:43,510
Is Lu Ming home?

125
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:45,150
He's not with you?

126
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:49,090
He went out early this morning.

127
00:12:49,150 --> 00:12:50,750
Did he go looking for Lin Hua?

128
00:12:52,030 --> 00:12:53,480
Well, I-I-I'll get going then.

129
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,010
Why are you looking for him?

130
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:57,610
Nothing. I just...

131
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:01,320
got bored staying home alone,

132
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,550
so I thought I'd ask him to take a walk.

133
00:13:03,670 --> 00:13:04,510
Go back inside and wait.

134
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:05,510
I'll go find him right now!

135
00:13:05,510 --> 00:13:06,110
Wait here.

136
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:06,790
No need, Auntie.

137
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:08,590
I'll just walk around by myself.

138
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:09,670
Bye.

139
00:13:10,180 --> 00:13:13,730
[Everlasting Bloom Florist]

140
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:29,150
[Death Certificate]

141
00:13:35,640 --> 00:13:37,460
He's not that unreliable.

142
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:39,680
Something urgent must have come up.

143
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,470
Any divers?

144
00:13:44,130 --> 00:13:44,880
What is it?

145
00:13:44,910 --> 00:13:46,030
Any divers?

146
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:47,930
Anyone?

147
00:13:49,270 --> 00:13:49,840
Can't do it.

148
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,790
Too dangerous.

149
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:52,440
Anyone?

150
00:13:55,090 --> 00:13:55,850
Me.

151
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,480
You look like a boiled chicken.

152
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,940
Have you done this before?

153
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:07,720
I have.

154
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,570
The drill bit broke in the pit.

155
00:14:10,570 --> 00:14:11,830
Are you doing it or not?

156
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:13,530
How much if I come back up?

157
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,280
How much if I don't?

158
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:17,220
If you come up, 6,000.

159
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,480
If you don't, 800,000.

160
00:14:22,790 --> 00:14:24,190
I want 20,000 if I come up.

161
00:14:25,950 --> 00:14:27,640
Are you out of your mind?

162
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:30,340
Anyone else want the job?

163
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,000
Two hundred thousand in exchange
for the lives of three of you.

164
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,030
Three lives, for heaven's sake!

165
00:14:37,890 --> 00:14:40,020
If I don't come up, I only want 200,000.

166
00:14:45,850 --> 00:14:46,680
You said it.

167
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:49,220
Come, let's get the gear.

168
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:30,320
Kid, it's not too late to back out now.

169
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:54,150
Pay up! Pay up!

170
00:16:55,910 --> 00:16:57,550
Calm down, everyone.

171
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,250
We're finding solutions for you.

172
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,030
We told you long ago.

173
00:17:02,030 --> 00:17:04,180
Don't put hydrogen tanks near the welding.

174
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,460
You didn't listen.

175
00:17:05,589 --> 00:17:06,920
The wiring got old.

176
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:08,240
No one replaced it.

177
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:10,170
Of course something went wrong.

178
00:17:10,349 --> 00:17:12,200
These were your responsibilities!

179
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:14,130
You have to compensate our losses!

180
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,750
It's because he was always trying to
cut corners at the factory.

181
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:19,510
Expired fire extinguishers
weren't replaced,

182
00:17:19,510 --> 00:17:21,680
which delayed firefighting efforts
after the explosion.

183
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,349
These were his responsibilities.

184
00:17:23,349 --> 00:17:25,079
They have nothing to do with me!

185
00:17:26,310 --> 00:17:27,400
Come, come.

186
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:28,440
Come, come.

187
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,160
Come, come.

188
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:29,680
Qiu.

189
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,440
Xia Xue.

190
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:31,680
You're finally here.

191
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:34,310
Qiu, what's wrong?

192
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:36,310
Well...

193
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:39,440
This accident

194
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:41,270
has a lot to do with your dad.

195
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:43,650
Your father died
in the shipyard explosion.

196
00:17:43,650 --> 00:17:45,050
He left me with this mess.

197
00:17:45,710 --> 00:17:47,370
What do you think we should do?

198
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:48,830
My dad?

199
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:49,790
Girl.

200
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,830
This was your dad's mistake.

201
00:17:51,830 --> 00:17:54,090
You have to take responsibility for him.

202
00:17:55,790 --> 00:17:57,920
Auntie, it has nothing to do with my dad.

203
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:59,510
Didn't you hear the manager?

204
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,590
The explosion happened because of issues
your dad was responsible for!

205
00:18:01,590 --> 00:18:03,850
-Exactly.
-It’s all because of your dad!

206
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,730
The oxygen is running out.
Why isn't he up yet?

207
00:18:44,050 --> 00:18:44,860
Pull.

208
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:55,350
Pull!

209
00:18:55,370 --> 00:18:57,530
It's stuck, it won't move!

210
00:19:56,940 --> 00:19:59,560
Lu Ming, stop sleeping. Wake up.

211
00:20:00,630 --> 00:20:03,420
Stop sleeping! Wake up.

212
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:06,400
Are you a pig? Still sleeping?

213
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:08,790
Lu Ming!

214
00:20:50,090 --> 00:20:51,780
Hurry, pull.

215
00:21:14,410 --> 00:21:16,370
Hurry. One, two, three.

216
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,130
You've got some serious luck.

217
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:55,370
You didn't move for so long.

218
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,940
I thought you were a goner.

219
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,440
I can't die.

220
00:22:26,070 --> 00:22:27,200
Everyone, calm down.

221
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,880
Let's talk this out. What's going on?

222
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,350
Lin Hua,

223
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,070
stop making trouble here.

224
00:22:31,070 --> 00:22:32,030
You're not Lu Ming.

225
00:22:32,030 --> 00:22:33,400
Why are you protecting her?

226
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:34,110
Yeah.

227
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,000
Why, are you guys dating?

228
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:37,340
Watch how you talk.

229
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,070
This has nothing to do with us either.

230
00:22:39,070 --> 00:22:40,440
We are victims too.

231
00:22:40,440 --> 00:22:43,310
Girl, just tell us
if you're paying up or not.

232
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:44,720
If you're not, we'll call the police.

233
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:46,110
Call the police!

234
00:22:46,110 --> 00:22:47,790
If you guys call the police,
it has nothing to do with us.

235
00:22:47,790 --> 00:22:49,440
It's not our problem.

236
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,750
What does it have to do with us?

237
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:53,010
We'll call the police!

238
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,200
Stop this. Stop!

239
00:22:58,030 --> 00:22:58,880
Who are you?

240
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:01,110
Who I am doesn't matter.

241
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:02,310
So many of you

242
00:23:02,310 --> 00:23:04,160
ganging up on a kid.

243
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:05,970
Don't you feel ashamed?

244
00:23:06,110 --> 00:23:07,550
Who we hassle is none of your business.

245
00:23:07,550 --> 00:23:08,920
-Are you okay?
-If you love meddling so much,

246
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,270
why don't you pay up instead?

247
00:23:10,270 --> 00:23:10,920
Exactly!

248
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:12,180
Who asked you to speak?

249
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:14,400
I'm Mr. Ma's secretary.

250
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:17,760
You should say less.

251
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:19,440
Yeah, let's go.

252
00:23:19,750 --> 00:23:20,960
Stop talking.

253
00:23:28,790 --> 00:23:29,680
Coming through.

254
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:30,510
Make way.

255
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:31,200
Make way.

256
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:36,830
Compensation for the deceased,

257
00:23:36,830 --> 00:23:38,240
medical costs for the injured,

258
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:40,600
and severance pay for laid-off workers.

259
00:23:40,620 --> 00:23:42,760
Mr. Ma has arranged everything.

260
00:23:43,270 --> 00:23:44,240
I can guarantee

261
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:45,440
that every single one of you

262
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:47,200
will get the money you deserve.

263
00:23:50,790 --> 00:23:52,510
If you keep surrounding this place

264
00:23:52,510 --> 00:23:53,880
and causing trouble,

265
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,790
I'll have to report to Mr. Ma

266
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:57,200
that you don't want a solution,

267
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:58,860
and just want to cause a scene!

268
00:23:59,110 --> 00:24:01,590
We do want a solution.

269
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,110
If you want a solution,

270
00:24:03,110 --> 00:24:05,040
then please wait patiently, okay?

271
00:24:05,310 --> 00:24:06,550
Think it through.

272
00:24:06,550 --> 00:24:08,640
All your problems can be solved!

273
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:11,720
Is what you said true?

274
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,500
Rest assured.

275
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:13,440
I keep my word.

276
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,960
If this isn't resolved, come find me!

277
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:17,200
Okay?

278
00:24:19,130 --> 00:24:20,790
Don't crowd here anymore.

279
00:24:20,790 --> 00:24:21,720
Go home for now.

280
00:24:22,350 --> 00:24:24,720
Wait for news. It'll be solved soon.

281
00:24:24,740 --> 00:24:26,720
Let's go. Break it up.

282
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,200
Wait.

283
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:35,760
Take this.

284
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,440
Regarding your father's unpaid wages,

285
00:24:40,440 --> 00:24:41,890
I will process them as soon as possible.

286
00:24:41,890 --> 00:24:43,220
If you have any trouble,

287
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,610
my number is on there. Just call me.

288
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:06,720
Don't listen to their nonsense.

289
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:10,200
Xia definitely had nothing
to do with the explosion.

290
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:11,490
It's all Qiu's fault.

291
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,300
Please don't take it to heart.

292
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:15,220
Why did you come alone?

293
00:25:15,270 --> 00:25:16,200
Where is Lu Ming?

294
00:25:17,290 --> 00:25:19,060
I went to his house to look for him.

295
00:25:19,060 --> 00:25:19,550
He...

296
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:20,750
He wasn't home.

297
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:22,410
Not home?

298
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,090
Go to work first.

299
00:25:26,510 --> 00:25:27,400
I'm going home.

300
00:25:45,170 --> 00:25:46,770
Here's ten thousand for now.

301
00:25:47,030 --> 00:25:48,560
I'm still earning the rest.

302
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,480
No, Lu Ming, are you kidding me?

303
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,330
Do you think you're paying off
a bank loan?

304
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:55,740
How about this?

305
00:25:56,250 --> 00:25:57,590
I'll write you an IOU.

306
00:25:57,590 --> 00:26:00,480
You're a murderer.
Talking to me about credit?

307
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:02,550
Write an IOU?

308
00:26:02,550 --> 00:26:05,210
Do you think you can write
an IOU for everything?

309
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:09,030
Xia Gang's compensation
will be dispensed soon.

310
00:26:09,030 --> 00:26:10,680
Maybe I'll ask Xia Xue!

311
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,090
This is my business.

312
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,620
Big, big, place your bets.

313
00:26:24,350 --> 00:26:25,480
Small, small, small!

314
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:27,480
Big, big, big!

315
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:30,750
I won!

316
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,680
Bets are locked.

317
00:27:05,160 --> 00:27:07,000
Please place your bets in order.

318
00:27:17,850 --> 00:27:20,450
Touch me again and see what happens.

319
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:22,200
See if I won't

320
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:23,720
expose your secret.

321
00:27:25,240 --> 00:27:26,570
If you get locked up,

322
00:27:26,750 --> 00:27:28,280
what will happen to Xia Xue?

323
00:27:30,260 --> 00:27:32,460
You'd let that cripple take care of her?

324
00:27:35,930 --> 00:27:37,780
When will you pay the rest?

325
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:40,070
One month.

326
00:27:40,070 --> 00:27:40,920
Five days.

327
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:43,950
If I don't get the money in five days,

328
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:46,440
I'll go straight to Ma Derong.

329
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:57,550
How did I lose again?

330
00:27:57,550 --> 00:27:59,410
I've lost all my savings.

331
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:08,110
Big, big, big!

332
00:28:21,110 --> 00:28:22,150
Got a light?

333
00:28:23,910 --> 00:28:24,660
No.

334
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:31,200
I realise you're pretty interesting.

335
00:28:33,350 --> 00:28:35,350
I've been watching you all night.

336
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:37,330
You've been wandering around,

337
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:39,600
looking everywhere but never betting.

338
00:28:39,830 --> 00:28:40,480
Are you scared

339
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,940
or are your pockets empty?

340
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:52,400
In Nanping, if you need money,

341
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,480
I'm the one to see.

342
00:28:57,470 --> 00:28:57,790
[Fu Wenchang, Sancheng Financial Services]

343
00:28:57,790 --> 00:28:59,200
They call me Chang.

344
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:01,110
Call me if you need anything.

345
00:29:07,070 --> 00:29:08,270
How much can I borrow?

346
00:29:23,510 --> 00:29:24,240
Chang.

347
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:30,160
Chang.

348
00:29:42,790 --> 00:29:43,990
Look, I'm about to...

349
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:48,960
180,000?

350
00:29:50,790 --> 00:29:51,400
So much?

351
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:58,920
[Sancheng Finance]

352
00:29:58,920 --> 00:29:59,920
Are you a student?

353
00:30:02,310 --> 00:30:03,720
[Sancheng Finance]

354
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:05,110
How much did you lose?

355
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:07,480
You're trying to win it back?

356
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:08,690
I don't gamble.

357
00:30:09,190 --> 00:30:10,450
And I don't know how to.

358
00:30:15,830 --> 00:30:16,480
I don't.

359
00:30:18,510 --> 00:30:19,550
You don't gamble or smoke.

360
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:21,110
So you're just watching
the pretty dealers deal?

361
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:21,880
Chang.

362
00:30:23,110 --> 00:30:24,770
How many times have I told you?

363
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:27,440
Be polite to customers.

364
00:30:31,030 --> 00:30:33,070
Look, you're borrowing so much money.

365
00:30:33,070 --> 00:30:34,530
You don't gamble or smoke.

366
00:30:35,270 --> 00:30:36,550
What do you need it for?

367
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:39,440
I have my own reasons.

368
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:43,120
Nine out, thirteen back.

369
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,680
He already explained it to me.

370
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:45,740
I understand that.

371
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:52,360
Borrowing money is easy.

372
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:54,720
I can give it to you right away.

373
00:30:55,090 --> 00:30:57,240
So, let's-

374
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:02,240
How many times have I said it?

375
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,310
Be polite to customers!

376
00:31:06,050 --> 00:31:06,880
Let's calculate it

377
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:08,140
and write an IOU first.

378
00:31:09,090 --> 00:31:10,220
This way.

379
00:31:13,830 --> 00:31:14,480
Chang.

380
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:16,280
Make tea.

381
00:31:18,070 --> 00:31:19,510
About the explosion case,

382
00:31:19,510 --> 00:31:21,570
the police are still investigating.

383
00:31:21,590 --> 00:31:23,510
As a family member of a victim,

384
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,720
we hope you will find peace

385
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,110
and cooperate with us

386
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:32,110
to comfort the families

387
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,610
of the deceased shipyard workers.

388
00:31:46,030 --> 00:31:47,200
You've seen the car.

389
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,270
You heard what Li Dong said.

390
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:50,550
It's not me saying

391
00:31:50,550 --> 00:31:52,510
that my son didn't die at the scene.

392
00:31:52,510 --> 00:31:54,840
The witnesses and evidence are all there.

393
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:02,750
Although I...

394
00:32:04,110 --> 00:32:06,270
signed the death certificate,

395
00:32:08,350 --> 00:32:10,550
if there is a one in ten thousand chance,

396
00:32:11,030 --> 00:32:12,920
I must find my son.

397
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:15,480
I must.

398
00:32:49,070 --> 00:32:50,440
Let go. Hands off!

399
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:52,000
Move!

400
00:32:52,350 --> 00:32:53,350
Let go!

401
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:50,270
Nobody move!

402
00:33:57,100 --> 00:33:58,290
Lu Ming.

403
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:02,380
Here to deliver the money?

404
00:34:07,270 --> 00:34:09,630
You didn't rob a bank, did you?

405
00:34:13,989 --> 00:34:14,989
Where is the tape?

406
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:17,230
What's the rush?

407
00:34:18,110 --> 00:34:19,840
I'll go get it for you right now.

408
00:34:42,739 --> 00:34:44,130
It's brilliant.

409
00:34:45,389 --> 00:34:46,139
Look.

410
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,730
Look at what you've done.

411
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:50,850
You guys are really something.

412
00:34:55,130 --> 00:34:55,860
Give it to me.

413
00:35:07,690 --> 00:35:09,220
If a third person finds out,

414
00:35:10,070 --> 00:35:11,030
even if I die,

415
00:35:11,870 --> 00:35:13,330
I'll drag you down with me.

416
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,670
Okay.

417
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,170
Lu Ming.

418
00:36:00,240 --> 00:36:00,920
Lu Ming!

419
00:36:03,590 --> 00:36:04,190
Lu Ming!

420
00:36:07,080 --> 00:36:08,210
How did this happen?

421
00:36:09,810 --> 00:36:12,470
Come on, I'll take you to the hospital.
Let's go.

422
00:36:12,820 --> 00:36:13,820
I'm fine.

423
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:18,440
Lu Ming.

424
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:21,630
What have you been doing lately?

425
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:25,550
Nothing.

426
00:36:28,230 --> 00:36:28,960
Okay.

427
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:32,250
You won't tell the truth, will you?

428
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,320
I'll go get Xia Xue

429
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:36,320
and see if she believes what you say.

430
00:36:36,630 --> 00:36:37,320
Lin Hua!

431
00:36:40,540 --> 00:36:41,740
Are you going to talk?

432
00:36:51,300 --> 00:36:53,830
The camcorder we took up
the mountain that day

433
00:36:57,470 --> 00:36:58,870
was picked up by Li Dong.

434
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:04,940
What did it record?

435
00:37:14,170 --> 00:37:15,220
What does he want?

436
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:17,120
Don't worry about it.

437
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,840
I've already handled it.

438
00:37:18,840 --> 00:37:20,590
Borrowed from loan sharks to fix it?

439
00:37:20,590 --> 00:37:22,320
This has nothing to do with you.

440
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:23,620
Stay out of it.

441
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:25,080
Remember,

442
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,670
Xia Xue must never know.

443
00:37:38,570 --> 00:37:44,620
[Flower Shop]

444
00:37:45,220 --> 00:37:47,530
[Flower Shop]

445
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,000
Lu Ming.

446
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:03,130
How did you get hurt?

447
00:38:07,440 --> 00:38:08,240
It's nothing.

448
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:10,740
I just got into a fight.

449
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:19,460
Let's go for a walk.

450
00:38:45,620 --> 00:38:48,410
♪ The sunset lingers on my left cheek ♪

451
00:38:52,500 --> 00:38:55,480
♪ Like words that stop
just short of being said ♪

452
00:38:58,930 --> 00:38:59,550
♪ I hide all my thoughts
in the old phone ♪

453
00:38:59,550 --> 00:39:01,030
When we first came back,

454
00:39:03,550 --> 00:39:04,480
we wanted to swim to the other shore,

455
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:06,590
♪ And say, as if it's nothing,
"How have you been lately?" ♪

456
00:39:06,590 --> 00:39:07,480
but before long,

457
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:09,670
a wave pushed us back.

458
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:12,220
Thinking about it now,

459
00:39:13,110 --> 00:39:13,460
we were like

460
00:39:13,460 --> 00:39:14,800
♪ Just a "long time no see" ♪

461
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:16,600
a boat without sails on this sea.

462
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:19,440
We couldn't have reached the shore.

463
00:39:20,140 --> 00:39:22,430
♪ After all these years ♪

464
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:24,660
We can do it.

465
00:39:26,820 --> 00:39:30,090
♪ The platform lights
flicker on and fade ♪

466
00:39:30,630 --> 00:39:31,820
I've never been superstitious,

467
00:39:31,820 --> 00:39:32,880
♪ When I open my eyes again,
you're already gone ♪

468
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:35,230
but after all that's happened,

469
00:39:36,670 --> 00:39:38,030
I feel like I'm just

470
00:39:39,670 --> 00:39:41,070
someone who's very...

471
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:42,800
♪ Goodbye or never again ♪

472
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:44,060
What are you thinking?

473
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:48,400
I'm serious.

474
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:50,980
♪ We'll meet again someday ♪

475
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:57,240
♪ Whether I hope for it or not ♪

476
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:00,030
Do you trust me?

477
00:40:01,850 --> 00:40:04,350
♪ I'll face it calmly all the same ♪

478
00:40:08,590 --> 00:40:11,040
♪ You ask me where I'm going next time ♪

479
00:40:15,440 --> 00:40:16,320
Xia Xue.

480
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,320
Actually, I had

481
00:40:22,030 --> 00:40:23,880
prepared a proposal speech.

482
00:40:25,920 --> 00:40:27,610
But now I feel those words

483
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,290
aren't important anymore.

484
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,480
In my life,

485
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:35,900
I've made many decisions.

486
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,630
But never one like today

487
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:42,650
that made me question myself repeatedly.

488
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:51,000
Because you're the best girl in the world.

489
00:40:55,940 --> 00:40:57,780
You deserve to have

490
00:40:58,190 --> 00:41:00,050
all the good things in this world.

491
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:19,240
Let me protect you for life.

492
00:41:22,740 --> 00:41:24,380
Marry me, Xia Xue.

493
00:42:23,060 --> 00:42:28,610
[Half a month later]

494
00:42:29,030 --> 00:42:29,760
Xia Xue.

495
00:42:38,110 --> 00:42:39,280
I made you some soup.

496
00:42:39,710 --> 00:42:41,040
Drink it while it's hot.

497
00:42:44,070 --> 00:42:44,960
What's wrong?

498
00:42:46,280 --> 00:42:47,670
I'm a little tired.

499
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,600
Come on, taste it while it's hot.

500
00:42:57,710 --> 00:42:58,590
How is it?

501
00:43:01,510 --> 00:43:04,040
My mom told me to make sure
I watch you drink it.

502
00:43:10,880 --> 00:43:11,480
Also,

503
00:43:13,150 --> 00:43:14,400
I still have some things to do.

504
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,590
Once I'm done,

505
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:17,660
we can buy tickets back to school.

506
00:43:28,710 --> 00:43:29,480
Take your time drinking it.
